<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-07-03T09:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-07-03T09:00:00-05:00" n="508" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d508">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">550.S1/1086: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to President <persName type="to">Roosevelt</persName>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-07-03T10:00:00-04:00">July 3,
                                    1933—10 a.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>38. Your 20, July 2, 10 p.m. Secretary Hull telephoned this morning that
                            he issued at 10:45 a.m., London time, the statement from you transmitted
                            in your 19, July 2, 6 p.m.</p>
                        <pb facs="0781" n="679" xml:id="pg_679"/>
                        <p>He decided that it would be inadvisable to add anything thereto and
                            therefore has not issued his proposed statement as Secretary of State
                            which was transmitted to you in the Department’s No. 37, July 2, 4
                                p.m.<note n="13" xml:id="d508fn13">See telegram No. 88, July 2, 8
                                p.m., from the Chairman of the American delegation, <ref target="#pg_674">p. 674</ref>.</note>
                        </p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Carr</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>